Sentencas: In this work, current leakage of the micro-tubular cells with a 10-mu m Ce0.9Gd0.1O1.95 (GDQ electrolyte based on cathode- and anode-supported configurations was investigated at 500 and 550 degrees C.
Titulo: Investigation of Current Leakage of Micro-tubular SOFCs with a Ceria Membrane for Low-intermediate Temperature Power-generation Applications

Sentencas: It was found that the open circuit voltage (V-OC) of the GDC membrane cell greatly corresponds to the cell structure, particularly influenced by the electrode polarization.
Titulo: Investigation of Current Leakage of Micro-tubular SOFCs with a Ceria Membrane for Low-intermediate Temperature Power-generation Applications

Sentencas: Calculations derived from the experimental results showed that the leak current through the GDC electrolyte gradually vanished as the external current increased to certain degree, which accordingly related to the polarizations, due to the cell structures.
Titulo: Investigation of Current Leakage of Micro-tubular SOFCs with a Ceria Membrane for Low-intermediate Temperature Power-generation Applications

Sentencas: The anode-supported cell can be capable of generating a high power density with a reasonable maximum-efficiency.
Titulo: Investigation of Current Leakage of Micro-tubular SOFCs with a Ceria Membrane for Low-intermediate Temperature Power-generation Applications

Sentencas: On the other hand, not only V-OC but also cell output and efficiency were significantly lowered for the cathode-supported cell.
Titulo: Investigation of Current Leakage of Micro-tubular SOFCs with a Ceria Membrane for Low-intermediate Temperature Power-generation Applications

Sentencas: It suggests that an appropriate cell structure is necessary to make the doped ceria a promising electrolyte for low-intermediate temperature power-generation applications.
Titulo: Investigation of Current Leakage of Micro-tubular SOFCs with a Ceria Membrane for Low-intermediate Temperature Power-generation Applications
